## 6. Assumptions & Constraints (Technical / Formal)

- 6.1 Assumptions
    - The dataset represents a useful snapshot of the 2024–2026 job market (based on the collected postings).
    - Salary values are normalized into **₹ LPA** for consistent benchmarking.
    - “Industry/sector,” “work mode,” and “experience level” are standardized during cleaning for accurate comparisons.
- 6.2 Constraints
    - Job portals and company pages have inconsistent formats, which affects scraping consistency.
    - Many job listings do not disclose salary; salary analysis is limited to records where salary is present/derivable.
    - Dashboard performance depends on Power BI model design and local machine resources when viewed in Desktop.

