### 8.1 Requirements table (BR format)

| BR ID | Requirement | User Story | Acceptance Criteria (Specific) |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **BR‑01** | Filtering by city/sector/role/experience/work mode/company type | **As a fresh graduate, I want to filter by city, so that I can focus on jobs in my preferred location.** | Filters must work across all pages and support slicing the full dataset of **5,247 listings** without breaking visuals. |
| **BR‑02** | Market overview KPIs (total listings, city split, sector split, work mode, experience) | **As a student/job seeker, I want an instant market snapshot, so that I can understand where demand is.** | Page must show total listings = **5,247**, and include city share (e.g., Bangalore **28%**) and sector share (IT **35%**). |
| **BR‑03** | Salary analytics (min/max/avg, comparisons) | **As a fresher, I want salary benchmarks by sector and role, so that I can set realistic expectations.** | Salary cards must show overall range **₹0.8–₹115.4 LPA** and average **₹19.83 LPA**, updating based on filters. |
| **BR‑04** | Entry-level (0–1 years) dedicated insights | **As a fresher, I want a dedicated view for entry-level roles, so that I’m not comparing myself to senior roles.** | Entry-level page must only include records labeled as **0–1 years** (as per the dataset standardization rules). |
| **BR‑05** | Company benchmarking + company-type comparison | **As a job seeker, I want to compare Unicorns vs MNCs, so that I can decide where to apply first.** | Dashboard must show the finding: **Unicorns pay ~15% more than MNCs** (based on the model’s aggregation). |
| **BR‑06** | Metric definitions & transparency | **As a career counselor, I want definitions for KPIs, so that I can trust and explain the numbers.** | All major KPIs should have definitions (tooltip or a definitions section). |
| **BR‑07** | Documentation + reproducibility for recruiters | **As a recruiter, I want to see the methodology, so that I can evaluate BA thinking, not just charts.** | GitHub link must be referenced and documentation must explain data collection, cleaning rules, and KPI logic. |
