## 12. Risks & Mitigation (What Actually Happened) ⚠️

| Risk / challenge I faced | Why it mattered | What I actually did (mitigation) |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Data inconsistency across sources | Same role/sector labeled differently | Standardized categories and created mapping rules in SQL |
| Salary data often missing | Salary averages can be misleading | Treated missing salary separately; ensured salary KPIs only use valid salary rows |
| Manual verification needed | Scraped data can include noise | Used manual curation checks for key fields |
| Outliers distort salary benchmarks | A few high values skew averages | **Excluded outliers > ₹50 LPA** for specific benchmarking views and used validation rules in SQL |

